Barcodes. The populations from low altitudes (< 600 m , ex
Limonium
) and those from higher altitudes (> 1400m , ex
Armeria
) build two incompletely separated clusters with average barcode distances of 0.6–0.7% and an average distance between these clusters of 1.6%. However, some specimens from Pto. Guadarrama and Sierra de Guillimona do not cluster together with others from higher altitudes. The maximum intraspecific barcode distance is 2.6%.

Distribution. Iberian Peninsula, including Spain and Portugal (Špatenka, 1992, Laštůvka & Laštůvka 1995 , 2001 , 2007 , 2014 ,
Špatenka et al. 1999
).
